The paper deals with the computational complexity of functions, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The references cited in the abstract are all related to complexity theory, and the paper presents new results on the space complexity of Turing machines. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions classical theorems on complexity, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of references from information theory (cs.IT) and logic (cs.LO) also indicates that these sub-categories are possible.
